Fix termstyle.auto() with replaced sys.stdout.

Some "interpreters" such as bpython override sys.stdout, but don't provide a
isatty method.  This stops auto() raising a missing attribute error.

0.1.3: source dist instead of egg

Added bg_default style, which enables transparency

In supported terminals bg_default will allow the background to be seen
behind the text.

Added italic style support.

Modern terminals, such as rxvt-unicode, have good italic display
support.
Added a ECMA-048 link to the documentation.

Underscore should be Style(4) according to ECMA-048.

Underscoring now works with standard terminals, sych as xterm or
rxvt-based ones, with this fix.
